<HL> Royex Gold to Buy
36% Stake in Lacana
For $52.3 Million</HL>
<DD> 02/06/87</DD>
<SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO>
<IN> T.RGM LCNAF T.WMI
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN>
<DATELINE> TORONTO  </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Royex Gold Mining Corp. said it agreed to purchase a 36% interest in Lacana Mining Corp. for about $52.3 million (Canadian). 

   Royex said it will purchase 4,751,009 Lacana common shares at $11 a share, and that the transaction is scheduled to close Feb. 13. 
Royex also said it plans no follow-up offer to the remaining shareholders of Lacana, which is based here. 

   Most of the shares will be purchased from Calgary, Alberta-based Westmin Resources Ltd., with the balance from other shareholders, Royex said. 
Westmin said it agreed to sell its block of 3.2 million shares to Royex for $34.7 million. 

   Royex said it will operate Lacana, which has interests in precious metals mining in Canada, Mexico and the U.S., as a separate unit. 
Royex operates gold mines in Canada and the U.S. Westmin is an energy and mining concern. 

   In Toronto Stock Exchange trading yesterday, Lacana closed at $10.50, down 25 cents. 
Westmin closed unchanged at $9.125, and Royex common closed at $4.15, up 5 cents. 

